---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Tanzania Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/tanzania/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kenya for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kenya' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Mauritius for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/mauritius' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'tanzaniaFit', header: 'Tanzania Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS 750,000-1,080,000/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS 885,000-1,265,000/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS 690,000-990,000/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS 630,000-905,000/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Tanzanian Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'TZS 150,000-400,000/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'TZS 630,000-1,080,000', annual: 'TZS 7.6M-13M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'TZS 865,000-1,430,000', annual: 'TZS 10.4M-17.2M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'TZS 1.17M-1.93M', annual: 'TZS 14M-23.2M' },
  { category: 'Tanzania Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'TZS 50,000-150,000/visit' },
  { category: 'Tanzania Public', monthly: 'Subsidized', annual: 'Basic quality' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tanzania 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Tanzania. Serengeti safaris, Zanzibar beaches, Mount Kilimanjaro, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tanzania"
  subheadline="Tanzania offers Serengeti wildlife, Zanzibar spice islands, Mount Kilimanjaro views, and African adventure—East Africa premier safari destination with Indian Ocean beaches."
  heroImage="/images/countries/tanzania-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Tanzania</h2>
  <p>
    Tanzania offers African adventure—Serengeti migrations, Ngorongoro crater, Mount Kilimanjaro, and Zanzibar beaches. For wildlife enthusiasts, it is unmatched. English is widely spoken, making it accessible. Zanzibar offers tropical island retirement with Stone Town charm.
  </p>

  <p>
    Dar es Salaam is the main city with best healthcare. Arusha is safari gateway with pleasant highland climate. Zanzibar offers island living with historic Stone Town. Moshi sits at Kilimanjaro base. Each location offers distinct lifestyle and access considerations.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Nairobi for complex care</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Swahili; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> TZS 2.5M-6M/month (~$1,000-2,400); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical coast; temperate highlands</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Safari; wildlife; beaches; adventure</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Generally safe; stable country</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Tanzania Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Tanzania healthcare is limited—developing country with basic facilities. Aga Khan Hospital in Dar es Salaam is best private option. Arusha and Zanzibar have adequate clinics for routine care. Complex conditions require evacuation to Nairobi, Kenya (1-hour flight) or South Africa.
  </p>

  <p>
    International insurance with Kenya/South Africa evacuation is essential. Many expats use Nairobi for serious healthcare—Nairobi Hospital, Aga Khan Nairobi are excellent. Local clinics handle routine care well.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Nairobi Healthcare Hub</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Nairobi, Kenya is the healthcare hub for Tanzania expats—world-class hospitals 1 hour by flight. Aga Khan Nairobi, Nairobi Hospital handle complex care. International insurance must include Kenya coverage. Plan for Nairobi visits for serious healthcare needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Tanzania has various residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit (Class C)</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees and those with independent means. Demonstrate sufficient income ($1,500+/month) or savings. Issued for 2 years, renewable. Application through Immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Investment Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Property investment or business establishment can support residence application. Popular among those buying property in Zanzibar.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Visitor</h3>
  <p>
    Tourist visa (90 days) extendable. Some retirees maintain long-term visitor status while exploring formal residence options.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Tanzania:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence permit:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Essential given limited local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Kenya evacuation:</strong> Critical for serious care</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa:</strong> For complex procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Tanzania</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Africa coverage including Kenya and South Africa is essential. Local healthcare handles routine needs; Nairobi handles moderate-serious cases. Plan for regional medical travel as normal healthcare approach.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Tanzania, Africa coverage with evacuation is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Tanzania</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Africa network, Nairobi/SA access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Africa expertise, regional knowledge</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good evacuation network</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with Africa evacuation essential for Tanzania.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Tanzania are moderate given need for regional coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local care is affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Consultations TZS 50,000-100,000; affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Africa regional:</strong> Cover Africa rather than worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Nairobi trips:</strong> Combine with healthcare; regular flights</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Wildlife Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,400/month pension. Safari lifestyle, Arusha base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Class C residence. Cigna Global with Kenya/SA evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~TZS 900,000/month (~$360). Safari country; Nairobi accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Zanzibar Couple, Both 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension £3,200/month. Zanzibar island life, Stone Town.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Zanzibar clinics routine; Dar/Nairobi serious.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~TZS 2.2M/month combined (~£900). Spice island; tropical paradise.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Dutch Adventure Seeker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,600/month pension. Part-time safari guide, Moshi base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Africa coverage. Kilimanjaro views daily.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Allianz ~TZS 780,000/month (~€310). Mountain life; adventure retirement.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Tanzania safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally yes—stable country, welcoming to visitors. Zanzibar and tourist areas are safe. Dar es Salaam has some crime; standard urban precautions. Political stability is good. Wildlife areas have natural risks (follow guide instructions). Most expats feel safe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Zanzibar different from mainland?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—semi-autonomous with own government. Muslim majority (versus Christian mainland). Stone Town is UNESCO heritage. More tourism-focused. Distinct character and culture. Ferries and flights connect to Dar es Salaam. Popular expat destination.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How often would I need Nairobi for healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Depends on health—routine care local, serious needs Nairobi. Many expats schedule annual check-ups in Nairobi. Emergency evacuation covered by insurance. Flights are frequent (1 hour, ~$150-250). Plan for 2-4 Nairobi healthcare trips per year if proactive.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I do safaris regularly as a resident?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—resident rates are much cheaper than tourist rates. Serengeti, Ngorongoro, Selous are accessible. Arusha-based retirees have easy safari access. Many expats explore multiple parks over time. Unique lifestyle benefit of Tanzania retirement.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes with Africa evacuation coverage for Tanzania.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Tanzanian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
